news.title: VOX LINERIO SLAT PANELS- The Perfect Blend of Elegance and Functionality for Modern Interiors
news.para: At VOX, we offer inspiration, expert guidance, and complete interior design solutions, including coordinated sets of ceilings, walls, and flooring.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to build 2,500 new homes under Ramai Housing Scheme in FY26
news.para: The scheme, aimed at providing housing for Scheduled Castes and Neo-Buddhists, has already helped 5,795 families secure new homes.

news.title: Noida authority initiates the process of returning residential plots to 2,200 farmers
news.para: Officials said the case — marked by not just legal battles but bureaucratic hurdles too since the early 2000s — represented one of the longest-running land disputes in the region.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue department says ‘One State, One Registration’ scheme to be delayed
news.para: "It may take more than three to four months to ensure smooth rollout of the scheme," said a senior official of the revenue department, citing technical challenges delaying its statewide launch.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM urges all urban local bodies to offer uniform services to residents
news.para: Instructing officials to evolve a common fee structure, Yogi asked senior officers to begin working on the action plan. Currently, for instance, wide gaps can be seen in property transfer fees charged by different local bodies.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to geotag 24.46 lakh properties
news.para: Under the project, 18.30 lakh residential and 6.16 lakh non-residential properties will be geotagged, and an aerial 3D digital map of the city will also be created.

news.title: Tesla leases office space in Mumbai’s Kurla
news.para: The US-based EV major has leased a 30-seater office in a co-working hub located in Phoenix Market City with a monthly rental of Rs 3 lakh, marking a key step in setting up its local operational infrastructure.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP carries out demolition drive around Sultanpur park
news.para: During the operation, two under-construction structures, 18 damp proof courses (DPCs), three farmhouse boundary walls, one industrial unit and five plot boundary walls were demolished.

news.title: Bengaluru property owners urge BBMP to extend 5% tax rebate
news.para: Residents argue that the BBMP property tax portal was inactive until April 5 due to technical glitches, leaving taxpayers with less time to make their payments.

news.title: Illegal layout properties to be confiscated, warns Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: Following a departmental review meeting, revenue minister Krishna Byregowda Friday said the decision follows strict directions from Supreme Court, which have been reiterated by chief minister Siddaramaiah.

news.title: Five more FIRs against Ansal Group in Lucknow for ₹5.78 crore fraud
news.para: So far about 70 cases has been lodged against the real estate firm in multi million land scam case. According to city-based businessman Sanjeev Agarwal , he paid Rs 5 crore in 2022 for a land deal.

news.title: Maharashtra appoints 12 officers to speed up Rs 912 crore MahaRERA recovery for buyers
news.para: The appointments, made under district collectors in six key districts, are intended to accelerate the compensation process under provisions of the Maharashtra Land Revenue Code, 1966.

news.title: Deadline gone, no fines yet for unregistered lifts in Noida
news.para: In Noida, around 5,700 lifts have been registered so far, while Ghaziabad has recorded about 1,750 registrations. However, officials estimate that Gautam Budh Nagar alone has over 80,000 lifts, indicating that a large number are yet to comply.

news.title: Delhi: RWA urges DDA to clear pending rent payments of 111 residents of Signature View Apartments
news.para: ​The Delhi Development Authority had earlier classified the 336-flat complex of Signature View Apartment in Mukherjee Nagar as a "dangerous building" due to structural safety concerns.

news.title: India Cements posts profit of Rs 14.68 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: However, its revenue from operations was down 3.11 per cent to Rs 1,197.30 crore in the March quarter of FY25. This was at Rs 1,235.74 crore in the corresponding quarter last fiscal.

news.title: Revised property tax can be paid even with previously received bills in Chandigarh
news.para: As per the completed technical exercise, the revised tax amounts were added to the system, following which the computer programme system will pick the new revised rates against each property through its allotted IDs.

news.title: Nagpur civic body collects Rs 259 crore property tax in FY25
news.para: The preference for offline payment suggests a persistent digital gap, despite the corporation offering higher rebates for online transactions.

news.title: Nagpur: Mhada’s prime civil lines project likely to undergo redevelopment
news.para: Revenue minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule expressed confidence that the Mhada building will be redeveloped, while officials said that currently discussions are at an advanced stage.

news.title: Bihar cabinet approves pre-feasibility report for six new airports
news.para: The cabinet also approved amendments to the Bihar Biofuels Production Incentive Policy, 2023, extending the application deadline to March 31, 2027 and financial sanction deadline to March 31, 2028.

news.title: Smart city works in Nashik to continue
news.para: The directorial board (DB) of the NMSCDCL on Friday gave its approval to the smart city corporation's proposal to amend norms to undertake works outside the smart city mission, either within or outside Nashik city.
